{
  "texts": [
    "For J 2 /J 1 < 1/2, we can interpret the field ϑ to be a coarse-grained version of the microscopic q-fold rotors θ j and carrying all their symmetry charges, but elevated to full angular freedom θ ∈ [0, 2π].",
    "The terms γ cos(qϑ), γ ′ cos(2qϑ),... can be interpreted as a soft implementation of the q-fold anisotropy, and thus γ, γ ′ are restricted to positive values to generate the correct set of q angular values.",
    "The field theory can be derived by replacing the original clock model with an anisotropic XY model [8,15] and following the recipe of Villain [94].For J 2 /J 1 > 1/2, our main regime of interest, the field ϑ corresponds to fluctuations atop the Z 2 NM order arising from OBD, and are not directly related to the lattice rotors.",
    "The coupling γ therefore is allowed to take positive and negative values.",
    "The former generates the exotic Z - q AFM order with seemingly prohibited expectation values."
  ]
}